193
00:14:28,354 --> 00:14:29,764
Whatever you're holding in...

194
00:14:29,771 --> 00:14:31,011
Let it out, you'll feel better

195
00:14:31,604 --> 00:14:32,604
let it out!

196
00:14:32,771 --> 00:14:36,093
When I was 8 I strayed from my mother

197
00:14:36,104 --> 00:14:38,811
and drifted, lost, through jing city

198
00:14:38,813 --> 00:14:40,644
I passed out from hunger

199
00:14:40,646 --> 00:14:42,557
your uncle happened to pass by

200
00:14:45,271 --> 00:14:49,719
I'll never forget that bowl of rice...

201
00:14:51,771 --> 00:14:53,978
I've been here over 20 years...

202
00:14:54,813 --> 00:14:56,349
Your days here

203
00:14:56,354 --> 00:14:58,015
have indeed been hard

204
00:14:58,896 --> 00:15:03,265
I owe you both my deepest gratitude

205
00:15:04,479 --> 00:15:06,094
uncle was a cruel man

206
00:15:07,063 --> 00:15:09,395
every time you tried to escape

207
00:15:09,854 --> 00:15:12,561
he beat you so hard you passed out

208
00:15:13,896 --> 00:15:15,056
this place

209
00:15:16,813 --> 00:15:19,225
is your prison, your cage

210
00:15:21,813 --> 00:15:23,019
press on it for me

211
00:15:31,438 --> 00:15:32,848
And after he died

212
00:15:34,021 --> 00:15:36,808
I put you through such brutal training

213
00:15:36,813 --> 00:15:39,099
you must hate me for it

214
00:15:40,979 --> 00:15:42,560
how could I hate you?

215
00:15:43,688 --> 00:15:46,020
I'd be willing to die in pieces

216
00:15:46,354 --> 00:15:49,346
to repay your gracious kindness

217
00:15:49,938 --> 00:15:53,101
it's Yang who should die in pieces

218
00:15:56,396 --> 00:15:58,057
if you kill him

219
00:15:58,063 --> 00:15:59,928
I'll let you go home

220
00:16:26,854 --> 00:16:27,854
My husband

221
00:16:30,771 --> 00:16:33,558
uncle was so right to choose you

222
00:16:34,313 --> 00:16:36,725
besides looking just like me

223
00:16:36,729 --> 00:16:40,472
you're incredibly quick-witted

224
00:16:40,979 --> 00:16:43,971
since making your debut a year ago

225
00:16:44,271 --> 00:16:46,307
you've been so good you've fooled them all

226
00:16:49,479 --> 00:16:51,344
sometimes I even wonder

227
00:16:51,813 --> 00:16:55,260
if my wife can still tell us apart?

228
00:17:05,396 --> 00:17:06,977
I've found your mother

229
00:17:11,188 --> 00:17:12,348
my mother

230
00:17:15,396 --> 00:17:17,182
she's still alive?

231
00:17:17,188 --> 00:17:19,144
She's still right there in jing

232
00:17:20,729 --> 00:17:23,721
wandering homeless in the streets

233
00:17:24,688 --> 00:17:26,929
I've bought your old house

234
00:17:28,521 --> 00:17:29,636
had everything set up

235
00:17:29,646 --> 00:17:30,931
she's settled in there now

236
00:17:31,146 --> 00:17:32,556
how did you find her?

237
00:17:33,104 --> 00:17:34,890
Does she know I'm still alive?

238
00:17:48,938 --> 00:17:50,769
So you have a huge stake

239
00:17:51,604 --> 00:17:52,969
in this battle

240
00:17:54,604 --> 00:17:56,390
after jing's taken

241
00:17:56,396 --> 00:18:00,264
you two can reunite

242
00:18:17,813 --> 00:18:19,474
Your zither needs tuning

243
00:18:27,313 --> 00:18:28,974
Yours is in the major key

244
00:18:28,979 --> 00:18:30,970
the strings need tightening

245
00:18:47,438 --> 00:18:48,723
Thank you

246
00:21:31,938 --> 00:21:32,938
You can go

247
00:21:47,479 --> 00:21:48,844
You've got just four hours

248
00:21:49,563 --> 00:21:51,303
to put this ointment on the wound

249
00:21:51,313 --> 00:21:53,395
you can't be a moment late

250
00:22:01,271 --> 00:22:02,636
Your husband

251
00:22:02,646 --> 00:22:04,511
is the most noble,

252
00:22:04,521 --> 00:22:05,761
most strategic,

253
00:22:05,771 --> 00:22:07,682
most admired man in pei

254
00:22:08,688 --> 00:22:09,688
and 1?

255
00:22:10,146 --> 00:22:11,761
But I'm nothing but a servant

256
00:22:12,188 --> 00:22:13,974
nothing more than his shadow

257
00:22:14,313 --> 00:22:15,428
you're not a shadow

258
00:22:18,146 --> 00:22:19,306
you are you

259
00:22:19,313 --> 00:22:21,224
who am I then?

260
00:22:26,521 --> 00:22:27,852
You were born in jing

261
00:22:28,813 --> 00:22:30,895
you yearn to go home

262
00:22:33,104 --> 00:22:34,264
maybe your mother

263
00:22:35,271 --> 00:22:37,227
is waiting at the Lane's end

264
00:22:38,021 --> 00:22:40,057
watching every passerby

265
00:22:40,604 --> 00:22:42,310
waiting for your return

266
00:22:48,813 --> 00:22:50,019
Many years ago

267
00:22:52,229 --> 00:22:53,765
my mother went blind

268
00:22:54,479 --> 00:22:56,344
she couldn't even see me

269
00:22:57,646 --> 00:22:59,227
if she were waiting there

270
00:23:02,354 --> 00:23:03,594
she could only listen,

271
00:23:04,521 --> 00:23:07,513
straining to hear the sound of my steps

272
00:23:09,854 --> 00:23:11,264
no earlier, no later

273
00:23:13,021 --> 00:23:14,977
you've suddenly found her,

274
00:23:16,688 --> 00:23:19,680
just in time to ensure I'll obediently

275
00:23:19,688 --> 00:23:21,394
fight this battle for you

276
00:23:25,479 --> 00:23:27,561
you've kept me caged in secret

277
00:23:28,104 --> 00:23:29,844
do you great, noble people

278
00:23:29,854 --> 00:23:31,936
know what scares me most?

279
00:23:32,521 --> 00:23:34,307
Darkness

280
00:23:35,604 --> 00:23:36,604
no one else

281
00:23:38,604 --> 00:23:39,639
no light

282
00:23:43,438 --> 00:23:44,553
no sound

283
00:23:45,396 --> 00:23:47,182
only me in total darkness

284
00:23:47,813 --> 00:23:49,019
I'd touch everywhere

285
00:23:49,313 --> 00:23:50,313
touch everything

286
00:23:51,354 --> 00:23:53,936
rub every tiny crack in the wall

287
00:23:53,938 --> 00:23:55,678
to keep from going mad

288
00:23:56,271 --> 00:23:58,387
to prove to myself I was still alive

289
00:24:03,854 --> 00:24:10,054
And so you always sleep on the floor

290
00:24:11,688 --> 00:24:13,770
with the lamp lit all night

291
00:24:37,896 --> 00:24:39,727
It's time for you to go to court

292
00:24:42,188 --> 00:24:47,182
the great hall of pei

293
00:24:55,771 --> 00:24:57,477
Who wishes to speak?

294
00:25:03,021 --> 00:25:04,101
I, sire

295
00:25:04,729 --> 00:25:05,729
